  "description": "A defining feature of TCCC is that it treats context as clinically determinative. The same wound is not the same problem when you are under direct threat as when you have cover, time, light, and help.\nTCCC is often taught in three phases (names vary by doctrine and update cycle):\n¶1. Care Under Fire / direct threat Characteristics:\nThe casualty, responder, and unit may still be exposed to lethal threat. Time and dexterity are limited; prolonged clinical decision-making is not realistic. The primary goal is to end or escape the threat and move to a position where care is possible. Clinical implication:\n",
